FBIS3-54903 "drsov003_f_94007" FBIS-SOV-94-003 Document Type:Daily Report 5 Jan 1994 National Affairs Former Lvov Missile Base Sold to Private Firm LD0401194694 Kiev UNIAN in Ukrainian 1459 GMT 4 Jan 94 LD0401194694 Kiev UNIAN Language: Ukrainian Article Type:BFN [Text] Lvov -- At a conference of the "Lvivprylad" production association on 3 January, Vasyl Dzera, chairman of the Frankivskyy rayon executive committee and a member of the oblast council commission for checking on foreign trade activity of the oblast state administration, asserted that the oblast authorities has sold a missile base near Brody to the private firm "Konza" for $13,000. Apart from a missile silo the former nuclear base includes working independent thermal and power resources, purification structures, and independent power supply systems. According to Vasyl Dzera, the procurator general's office of Ukraine has instituted criminal proceedings regarding the sale of a former military facility by the oblast state administration to "Konza."
